    "name": "ASTM F1717 Compression-Bending Verification Requirement",
    "description": "The FEA model ensemble shall be verified against physical bench data generated through a controlled experiment conforming to ASTM F1717, with defined loading fixtures, specimen preparation protocols, environmental controls, and prospectively specified acceptance criteria (QoI difference <10%, E/uval <1.96). The verification method shall be a controlled experiment in which all independent variables are held fixed except the applied compressive-bending displacement, ensuring that observed QoI differences are attributable solely to model form and numerical error rather than uncontrolled environmental or operator factors.",
    "requiredVerificationMethod": "controlled-experiment"
