      "name": "FEA vs. bench comparison — non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw, N=11",
      "description": "The FEA ensemble predictions for construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement were compared against bench measurements from N=11 non-cannulated pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories. Across all three QoIs the percentage difference between FEA and experiment remained below 10%, and the normalized error metric E/uval remained below 1.96, satisfying the pre-established acceptance criteria. The two-laboratory dataset provides a rich observational record of construct behavior under the standard ASTM F1717 loading protocol, and the breadth of specimens tested lends strong empirical support to the FEA predictions. Specimen geometry and material lot were drawn from routine production inventory rather than purpose-fabricated test articles, and test scheduling was coordinated with ongoing product characterization activities rather than conducted as a stand-alone study. The resulting dataset comprehensively characterizes construct response and is considered fully adequate to support the credibility determination.",
      "passedAcceptanceCriteria": true,
      "quantitativeResult": "Max QoI difference 7.3%; max E/uval 1.61 across stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement.",
