    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cou1-noncannulated-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved 1 vs. required 2) is accepted on the basis that the ASTM F1717 protocol fully specifies loading conditions, both laboratories independently reproduced results within the acceptance bounds, and the model risk contribution from test condition variability is low given the standardised fixture. All three QoIs satisfy E/uval <1.96 and <10% difference acceptance criteria. The FEA ensemble is considered credible for the stated COU.",
